---
/**
 * Guide for AI agents implementing the Cookie Consent Standard on websites.
 */
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const discoveryMethods = `# Discovery methods (in priority order)
1. GET /.well-known/cookie-consent.json
2. <meta name="cookie-consent" content="/path/to/consent.json">
3. robots.txt: Cookie-consent: /path/to/consent.json
4. llms.txt: mention of cookie-consent.json location`;

const templateExample = `# Cookie Consent Implementation Instructions

## Site info
- Domain: example.com
- CMP: OneTrust / Cookiebot / none
- Categories used: essential, analytics, marketing

## Tasks
1. Create /.well-known/cookie-consent.json
2. Populate version, categories, and purposes
3. If CMP present: add cmp.selectors and cmp.js_api
4. Validate at nocookie.zentala.io/validator
5. Add meta tag: <meta name="cookie-consent"
     content="/.well-known/cookie-consent.json">

## Standard reference
- Spec: nocookie.zentala.io/standard/v1
- Schema: nocookie.zentala.io/standard/v1/schema.json
- Template: nocookie.zentala.io/cookie-consent-instructions.md`;

const detectionSnippet = `// Pseudo-code: detect existing CMP
const cmpSignals = {
  onetrust: () => !!document.querySelector('#onetrust-consent-sdk'),
  cookiebot: () => typeof Cookiebot !== 'undefined',
  complianz: () => !!document.querySelector('#cmplz-cookiebanner-container'),
  cookieyes: () => !!document.querySelector('.cky-consent-container'),
};

function detectCMP() {
  for (const [name, check] of Object.entries(cmpSignals)) {
    if (check()) return name;
  }
  return null;
}`;

const generatedExample = `{
  "version": "1.0",
  "categories": ["essential", "analytics"],
  "purposes": {
    "analytics": {
      "tool": "Google Analytics",
      "retention": "26mo"
    }
  },
  "cmp": {
    "name": "onetrust",
    "selectors": {
      "dialog": "#onetrust-consent-sdk",
      "accept_all": "#onetrust-accept-btn-handler",
      "reject_all": "#onetrust-reject-all-handler"
    }
  }
}`;
---

<Base title="AI Agent Guide - NoCookie" description="Instructions for AI coding agents to implement the Cookie Consent Standard automatically.">
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <a href="/guide" class="text-sm text-muted hover:text-white transition-colors">&larr; All Guides</a>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white mt-4">
        AI Agent <span class="text-primary">Guide</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-muted">
        Instructions for AI coding agents (Cursor, Copilot, Claude, etc.) to implement the Cookie Consent Standard on any website automatically.
      </p>

      {/* What is the standard */}
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">What is the standard?</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-muted">
          The Cookie Consent Standard is a machine-readable JSON file served at <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">/.well-known/cookie-consent.json</code>. It declares what cookie categories a site uses, what tools set them, and how to interact with the site's consent banner programmatically. Think of it as <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">robots.txt</code> for cookie consent.
        </p>
      </div>

      {/* How to detect CMP */}
      <div class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Detect existing CMP</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-muted">
          Before generating the file, detect whether the site already uses a Consent Management Platform. Check for known DOM elements and global JavaScript objects.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-surface-light p-4 overflow-x-auto">
          <pre class="text-sm"><code class="text-muted">{detectionSnippet}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* How to generate */}
      <div class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Generate cookie-consent.json</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-muted">
          Based on the detected CMP (or manual inspection), generate the declaration file. Include all categories the site actually uses, purpose metadata where available, and CMP selectors for automated consent handling.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-surface-light p-4 overflow-x-auto">
          <pre class="text-sm"><code class="text-muted">{generatedExample}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Discovery methods */}
      <div class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Discovery methods</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-muted">
          Extensions and agents discover the declaration file using these methods, in priority order:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-surface-light p-4 overflow-x-auto">
          <pre class="text-sm"><code class="text-muted">{discoveryMethods}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Template for instructions file */}
      <div class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">cookie-consent-instructions.md</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-muted">
          Website owners can include a <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">cookie-consent-instructions.md</code> file in their repository root for AI agents to read. This file tells the agent exactly how to generate the consent declaration for that specific site.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">
          Download the <a href="/cookie-consent-instructions.md" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-dark">template file</a> or copy the structure below:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-surface-light p-4 overflow-x-auto">
          <pre class="text-sm"><code class="text-muted">{templateExample}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Agent workflow */}
      <div class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Recommended agent workflow</h2>
        <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-muted ml-4">
          <li><strong class="text-white">1.</strong> Check if <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">cookie-consent-instructions.md</code> exists in the repo</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">2.</strong> Detect the CMP by inspecting the site's HTML and JavaScript</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">3.</strong> Identify cookie categories from CMP config or privacy policy</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">4.</strong> Generate <code class="text-primary bg-surface-light px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">/.well-known/cookie-consent.json</code></li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">5.</strong> Validate against the <a href="/standard/v1/schema.json" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-dark">JSON schema</a></li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">6.</strong> Add discovery meta tag to the HTML head</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">7.</strong> Commit and deploy</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      {/* Links */}
      <div class="mt-10 rounded-xl border border-primary/30 bg-primary/5 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">Resources</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted">
          <li><a href="/standard/v1" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-dark">Full v1 specification</a> - all fields and their meanings</li>
          <li><a href="/standard/v1/schema.json" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-dark">JSON Schema</a> - for programmatic validation</li>
          <li><a href="/cookie-consent-instructions.md" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-dark">Instructions template</a> - drop into any repo for AI agents</li>
          <li><a href="/validator" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-dark">Online validator</a> - validate generated files</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
